{
  "stem": "11801.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And when I could speak enough English, after that term when I attended nothing but English classes, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I told them that I should be in the 10th grade.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "By now I was 16.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And so they allowed me to go into the 10th grade.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I-- by taking extra courses and going to summer school, I finished high school in two years.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "So I graduated-- and I was so proud of that-- almost with my own age group.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I was very, very concerned.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I, I didn't want to be-- again, I didn't want to be different.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I wanted to be-- this became one of my goals, when I arrived in the United States.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "I didn't care anymore whether I was Jewish, whether I was Christian, whether I was black, whether I was white.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "You know, I just wanted to, to be left alone and not to be singled out and to just do my own thing, without being, you know, pointed out or, or talked about.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And yet, when I came, I had braids, which I wore on top of my head.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I had never worn makeup.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I was 16.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I had never worn stockings, so I-- and I rebelled against-- you know, my relatives immediately wanted me to get dressed and to wear lipstick, and, and-- I had humongous fights with my relatives, because I, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] you know, I wouldn't allow them to dominate me.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And yet they certainly tried.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And they thought that they had every right to do so, because they wanted to Americanize me.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "I understand what they were trying to do.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "I resented it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And yet I wanted to be like everybody else, but I must have stuck out like a sore thumb.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
